The first thing that struck me when I walked into Teak Wood was the great decor. With statues lining the tables and elaborate wooden decorations lining the walls, the restaurant looks elegant yet understated, and charming without being kitsch. I was immediately greeted by two servers who were very attentive the whole evening and gave me great tips on what to order. The red curry I ordered was served fast (in 10 minutes after ordering in fact!), and it tasted delicious. Perhaps it helped that I was there on a night with less traffic, but I was really impressed by the level of service. The only tiny bit of feedback I have is that I would have loved a bit more tofu in my red curry, but that's it. Great Thai food, great service, excellent ambience. Would recommend!

Very nice restaurant. My wife and I dined here on Christmas Eve so it was very quiet but the staff were very polite and the food was delicious. Healthy portions for the entrees and all the food we had was quality. My wife had the Pad See Ew and I had the Mango Curry with Chicken and we were both very happy with them. Definitely would recommend to any Thai lovers 👍🏻

I ordered online through GrubHub so I can't speak for the dining experience. The food was excellent though. It might come off as pricey at the start but the serving size is big and they do not skimp on flavor. The beef mango curry had huge chunks of mangoes, generous amount of beef and the curry itself was flavorful. The cashew prawn too didn't skimp on the shrimps and wasn't overloaded with veggies as extenders.

Great atmosphere, beautiful wood carvings, good food. I dined here with about 10 friends. We planned to pay individually but our waiter told us that a party of our size could only have one bill, which meant we had to split apart into smaller groups. That was silly, and after asking her if we could break apart but stay close together and then almost deciding to leave, she reluctantly allowed us to stay as one big group and still pay individually. The food did not take more than 40 minutes to arrive which was very great. I really enjoyed my meal, it was a carved out Pineapple filled with rice and shrimp. Great place, but we warned if you are planning to eat here with more than 8 people!

Completely disappointing experience despite friendly service If you have a GLUTEN issue this restaurant is NOT FOR YOU! Despite calling it THAI they seem to use gluten based soy sauce in all of their curries of other main dishes. This is unusual. Thai do not put soy sauce in curries. Thus no food for me except Vegetables dish or Pad Thai. The Pad Thai was very tasteless. I had to put add salt and hot spices to make it somewhat interesting. The beef was tough. I am now eating Thai all over the world since 35 years and this restaurant was the worst. Even for people with no gluten issue the food is unispiring and lacks spices, which normally make Thai food great. This was also evident with the Duck Dish my son ate. His portion was large we must say - but tasteless. It seems there are NO THAI cooks in this restaurant - which gets supported by the fact that they also specialize in Japanese Sushi. Waiters friendly and ambiente rustic-nice. Portions large. All in all very disappointing and NOT authentic at all.

Almost everything about teakwood is great. The food is very tasty and there is a wide variety. Even my mom who had never had Thai food and was not an adventurous eater enjoyed it. The ambiance is also incredible as the entire place is decorated in carved wood - statues, bas reliefs, and more. The main downside is that it is under DC's gay bathhouse which seems unsanitary. The wait staff (particularly the hosts) can also be rude so thankfully you don't have to deal with them much. Perhaps because of these two things the place never has a wait for really good food!

Teak Wood is great — far better than you'd think given that they can accommodate parties of any size pretty much any time of day. The space is big and nicely decorated. Drinks are better than those of similar restaurants. Prices are fair and the menu offers lots of variety. We've been a couple times and are pleased every time.
